      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TRIPLE PHANTOM (1) missed the frame latest (18.62) when fifth over 320m at Richmond in a Grade 5. Has already won two times from this draw. Has the ability and looks a key chance here. DENAWEN BEACH (8) stalked the lead from a low draw then burst clear to score (20.41) at Gunnedah in a Grade 5 over 340m. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Can make it back-to-back wins. COCO MAC (6) boasts a strong record this journey here with five wins and three minors from 11 tries. Was out of the placings last time (20.13) at Gunnedah in a NG, finishing seventh and beaten 9 lengths. Looks well placed here and among the chances. BOGAN KNOWS (3) will have admirers again after a narrow placing last time out.",
